This is **planckUi**, a headless React Native UI library shipped as a **pnpm monorepo** with **Turborepo**. The codebase enforces token-driven styling, fixed component file layout, and strict lint rules. For new core UI components, use `pnpm generate` (Plop) and follow **Component colocation** below. Before adding a named theme to the token pipeline, read `.cursor/skills/add-theme.md`. Before adding a hook under `packages/core`, read `.cursor/skills/add-hook.md`. Before authoring or updating Nextra docs, read `.cursor/skills/write-docs-page.md`.

Hard rules:
- Colocate UI: follow **Component colocation** in this file for `packages/core` components and mirror the same folder-per-feature pattern in `apps/example` and `docs` when adding or substantially editing UI.
- Never hardcode hex, `rgb()`, `hsl()`, or named CSS colors in `packages/core` (use `get{Name}Tokens` + theme scales only).
- Never use Expo, NativeWind, or Tailwind in this library.
- Never use the `any` type.
- Never import another workspace package via relative paths (always `@my-ui-lib/tokens`, `@my-ui-lib/core`, etc.).
- Never hand-edit `packages/tokens/src/generated/`; regenerate via the tokens package build.
- Before reporting a task complete, run `pnpm typecheck` and `pnpm lint` from the repo root (or the relevant package) and fix failures.
- At the start of a scoped task, read the matching skill file end-to-end and follow it literally.
- When adding a new component, variant, or navigator pattern, integrate it into docs in the same task: add/update the docs page, menu entry, live preview, and install/setup guidance.
- If the docs page offers copyable implementation code, update the docs source explorer / generated source sync so the new files are copyable too; docs preview-only support is not enough.

Package names:
- Tokens: `@my-ui-lib/tokens`
- Core: `@my-ui-lib/core`
- CLI: `@my-ui-lib/cli`
- Docs app: `@planckui/docs`
- Example app: `apps/example`

Key paths:
- Component token helpers → `packages/tokens/src/component-tokens.ts`
- `SemanticTokens` → `packages/tokens/src/semantic.ts`
- Theme JSON overrides → `packages/tokens/src/tokens.input/themes/`
- Core components → `packages/core/src/components/`
- Core hooks → `packages/core/src/hooks/`
- Core public API → `packages/core/src/index.ts`
- Docs MDX → `docs/pages/`
- Docs live preview shell → `docs/components/Preview.tsx`
- Plop templates → `plop-templates/`

## Component colocation (required)

Apply this layout everywhere new UI is added so each feature owns its styles, types, and tests in one place.

### `packages/core/src/components/`

- **Single public component** (e.g. `Avatar`): one folder `ComponentName/` containing:
  - `ComponentName.tsx` — implementation
  - `ComponentName.styles.ts` — `StyleSheet` / style helpers (token-driven; no stray hex in core)
  - `ComponentName.types.ts` — props and public types
  - `ComponentName.test.tsx` — tests next to the component
  - `index.ts` — **only** re-exports the public API (`export { … } from './ComponentName'`, `export type { … } from './ComponentName.types'` or from `./ComponentName` if types are re-exported there)
- **Implementation-only helpers** that exist solely for that component stay inside the same folder (extra `*.ts` / `*.tsx` files are fine if names are clear, e.g. split render modules).
- **Multiple related public components** under one product area (e.g. classic tabs vs Zepto tabs): use a **parent folder** (`Tabs/`) with:
  - `index.ts` — re-exports the family API consumed by `packages/core/src/index.ts` (or separate entry files)
  - **one subfolder per variant**, each subfolder repeating the same five-file pattern (`Tabs/Tabs/…`, `Tabs/ZeptoTabs/…`). Do not leave sibling `*.styles.ts` files loose at the parent root unless they are truly shared; prefer a shared `Tabs/shared/` only when needed.

### `apps/example`, `docs/`, and other packages

- Mirror the same habit: **one folder per screen, lab, or preview**; colocate `*.styles.ts`, `*.types.ts`, and tests with the main `*.tsx` instead of scattering files at package root.
- Prefer named files over dumping everything into a single huge component file when styles or types grow.

### Refactors and reviews

- When touching a component that predates this layout, **move it into the structure above** if the change is already editing that area (do not expand scope purely to reformat unrelated code).
- New work must not introduce parallel flat files (e.g. `Foo.tsx` next to `Foo/` without migrating).
